snippet.textDisplay: I like that you mention there is a subtheme about identity in TROS, but have you considered (and maybe I just haven't found it yet) that the trilogy is a triptych of the three lessons Luke says he will give Rey? TFA is the first lesson, that the Force is every where, in everything, etc, the second lesson is about failure, and TLJ is filled with failure, and TROS is the third lesson, facing your fears. Looking at this this way, I don't see how people can argue the producers didn't have a plan.
